                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-319-off1847 t18320405-319-victim2642"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-319-person2643">
                  ROBERT 
                  HAINES
               <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2643" type="surname" value="HAINES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2643" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2643" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep an eating-house in <placeName id="t18320405-319-crimeloc1849">High-street, Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-319-crimeloc1849" type="placeName" value="High-street, Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320405-319-crimeloc1849" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-319-off1847 t18320405-319-crimeloc1849"></join>. The prisoners came there together at twelve o'clock at night, on the 4th of April; there were two others in company with them, and they called for four basins of soup - they sat in the box in which the prosecutor sat asleep; I noticed them - Allen came in with a straw hat on; he went out with a black one - I went to look at the prosecutor, who lodges with me, and his hat was gone from the table where it had been laying; I suspected the prisoners, and went after them - I saw an officer, and described the parties; he brought Allen back first, and then got Murphy - the prosecutor was still asleep.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-319-person2644">
                  CHARLES 
                  BLAND
               <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2644" type="surname" value="BLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2644" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2644" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18320405-319-viclabel1850" type="occupation">sailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-319-victim2642 t18320405-319-viclabel1850"></join>. I was at the eating-house - I fell asleep. but I was not drunk; when I awoke my hat was gone, and my handkerchief, which had been in it - this is my hat; I did not see the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-319-person2645">
                  WILLIAM 
                  REEVES
               <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2645" type="surname" value="REEVES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2645" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2645" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable K 152.) I had information of this, and went down a dark street - I saw Allen with her hand behind her; I asked what she had got - she said, "My husband's hat;" I said, "How came you to have it?" she said, "I have had a row with him, he threw his hat at me, and ran away;" I took her to the<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183204050124"></xptr>eating-house, with the straw hat which she had in her hand - we left the hat there; she asked me to let her go, and she would find the man - she went on, and I followed her; she called Tim - he said, "Is that you?" she said,"Yes, you have got me into a nice piece of trouble about this hat;" he said, "Where is my hat?" she said, "The Policeman has it:" she went up to him - I followed her, and seized them both; he had no hat on then, but Criper found this hat within a few yards of where I took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-319-person2646">
                  ROBERT 
                  CRIPER
               <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2646" type="surname" value="CRIPER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2646" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-person2646" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a private watchman. At a quarter before one o'clock I was called to assist the officer, who had the prisoners in charge - we took them to the station; I then went to the lane again, and found this hat, but no handkerchief.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Murphy's Defence. I was going into the house, and this woman, who was a stranger, was going in; she asked me to treat her, and I did - we then went out, and had some words; I threw my hat at her, and never saw it again.</p>
               <p>MURPHY - <rs id="t18320405-319-verdict1851" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320405-319-verdict1851" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
               <p>
